<h1>@HI{{te ha ikemasenn}}</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<ol>
<li> @Vte{{}} <strong>@HI{{haikenai}}</strong>
</ol>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
This pattern is used to express prohibition.
</p>

<h2> Examples </h2>

<ol>
<li>
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{kokode tabakowo @KJ{{suck}}tteha ikemasenn. @KJ{{prohibition^smoke}}desu kara.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      You may not smoke here because it is a no-smoking area.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</ol>

<h2> Notes </h2>

<p>
To <em>strongly</em> refuse permission, use @HI{{iee, ikemasenn}}. This form cannot be used to
a superior.
</p>

<p>
A slightly stronger expression is @Vte{{}}@HI{{hanaranai}}.
</p>

